<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Re: TOPIC: MIN PVP LVL</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Koss">Koss</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 12:06 p.m. 15/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Re: TOPIC: MIN PVP LVL<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=907" TARGET=_self>TOPIC: MIN PVP LVL</A> (Geiger)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>They did this in Meridian 59, you could not attack other player until 30 hp (you start with 20). It might of worked, but there were too many ways in m59 for below 30 hp char to annoy other players. While they could not attack others, they could still heal others, truce the screen (ending all combat), scout around to learn where you were then relay that information back to your enemies, a few of them would stand in areas to block people off, purify you (gets rid of all your resist/shielding spells), spam areas to make people lose server or lag, the list goes on and on.. not to mention they could be incredibly rude and just be general annoying brats. Then again, the 3do programming department for Meridian 59 was just the most worthless lazy ass piece of shit group of programmers I have ever seen in my life(with the possible exception of Centipede, took em long enough!). Most of these things could of been fixed over night, and most likely would of been had it been Verant in charge. Still, im sure new problems would arise with the people being invulnerable to everyone else on a pvp server. We probably will not see them in the beta test but we sure will in the final. There may not be any of those UO-Type punks here now but they'll get here, rest assured.

<P>I just do not think its a smart idea to make players invulnerable on a pvp server, it totaly defeats the purpose. The newbie levels do not last long anyway, and getting pked as a newbie does not slow you down much at all. Not to say it does not hurt you, just that its better to learn the lesson then, rather than when your level 20 in full chain with 200 plat on ya heh heh.
<P>I think newbies are fine as they are, its not hard to learn a game even if there are rampant pkers. As newbies, we all survived UO and m59, and just like us, newbies will survive everquest too. If people need a place to learn the game, there are currently 5 other servers where another player can not touch you, something the rest of us never had in all the other games.
<P>Koss
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
